Author: PassionFruitYellow
Text: There's osfed which basically when you don't fit the criteria for AN, BN or BED but it is still enough to be an ED. But disordered eating even if it's not a full blown ED is damaging and could potentially spiral into an ED and should be treated before it does happen. Prevention is better than waiting till it gets to a more serious and less treatable state.

Author: tigerchik
Text: you're not alone. It sounds like you fall on the spectrum of some disordered eating tendencies.
